reviewText: Outnumbered raises the bar for domestic sitcoms. It's inspired, intelligent and hilarious. It absolutely captures modern times. I really can't watch the plodding Modern Family American shows. Each actor is strong and has great timing.Some network here needs to import this. Perhaps Greg Daniels could be the executive producer. He's done a great job with The Office.

reviewText: Quite cute, but intelligent show, Not mean spirited.  I get the idea that it is not entirely scripted; there is a 'behind the scenes' where they ask the kids what they'd do with a million.  The responses are brilliant, I hope they can use it in the show. If they can maintain that level of spontaneity it'll be in syndication forever.
